  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle, then peel lengths off your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> until you end up with a pile of courgette ribbons</p><p>Zest your <strong>lime[s] </strong>(try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter), then combine the juice of <strong>half </strong>your <strong>lime </strong>with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and a small splash of<strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>boiled water</strong> in a heatproof bowl and stir until the sugar has dissolved, add your <strong>courgette ribbons</strong> and set aside until serving – this is your <strong>quick-pickled courgette</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-48-1724338539642-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-48-1724338539642-x400.jpg",
