          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> with your <strong>cornflour</strong> in a jug, then add your <strong>fish sauce</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong> and <strong>red chilli relish</strong> with the <strong>lime zest</strong> and <strong>remaining juice</strong> and stir it all together – this your <strong>zesty soy sauce</strong></p><p>Once the pork is fragrant, add the <strong>zesty soy sauce </strong>and the <strong>chopped mint</strong> and <strong>coriander</strong> with <strong>half </strong>of your <strong>chopped peanuts </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) and cook for 1-2 min or until thickened and cooked through (no pink meat!) – this your <strong>Vietnamese-style lemongrass pork</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch it like a hawk to prevent the sauce from burning!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
